# 📌 Overview

Spam messages are one of the biggest challenges in modern communication systems. Traditional keyword-based filtering often fails because spammers constantly change message patterns.

This project builds an **end-to-end Machine Learning pipeline** that automatically classifies SMS messages into:

- 📩 Ham (Legitimate Message)
- 🚫 Spam (Unwanted Message)

The project covers the entire ML workflow including:

- Data Cleaning
- Exploratory Data Analysis
- Feature Engineering
- Text Preprocessing
- NLP
- TF-IDF Vectorization
- Model Training
- Model Comparison
- Ensemble Learning
- Model Selection

---

# 🎯 Problem Statement

Given an SMS message,

> Predict whether the message is **Spam** or **Ham** with maximum precision while minimizing false positives.

Since incorrectly classifying a genuine message as spam is more harmful than allowing a spam message through, **Precision** is treated as the primary evaluation metric.

---

# 📂 Dataset

### SMS Spam Collection Dataset

- **Total Messages:** 5,572
- **Target Classes:** 2
- **Spam**
- **Ham**

Dataset contains two columns

| Column | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| label | Spam / Ham |
| message | Raw SMS text |

