# 🧹 Data Cleaning

The dataset was cleaned by:

- Removing unnecessary columns
- Renaming columns
- Handling missing values
- Removing duplicate records
- Resetting dataframe index

---

# 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis

Performed several visualizations to understand the dataset:

### Distribution of Classes

- Majority of messages are Ham
- Dataset is imbalanced

### Message Length Analysis

Created new features:

- Number of Characters
- Number of Words
- Number of Sentences

Compared these distributions for Spam and Ham messages.

### Word Frequency

Generated

- WordCloud for Spam
- WordCloud for Ham

### Most Common Words

Top frequent words were extracted separately for

- Spam messages
- Ham messages

---

# ⚙ Text Preprocessing Pipeline

Each message goes through the following pipeline:

```
Raw Text
     │
Lowercase
     │
Tokenization
     │
Remove Special Characters
     │
Remove Stopwords
     │
Remove Punctuation
     │
Stemming
     │
Processed Text
```

### Libraries Used

- NLTK
- Porter Stemmer
- stopwords corpus

---

# 🧠 Feature Engineering

Additional numerical features were created:

- Number of Characters
- Number of Words
- Number of Sentences

These helped in understanding the data although the final classifier primarily relies on TF-IDF features.

---

# 📝 Text Vectorization

Text cannot be directly used by machine learning algorithms.

Therefore,

**TF-IDF Vectorizer** was used.

```
Raw Text

↓

TF-IDF

↓

Sparse Feature Matrix

↓

Machine Learning Model
```

Configuration

- TF-IDF Vectorizer
- max_features = 3000

---

# 🤖 Machine Learning Models Tested

The project compares multiple classification algorithms.

| Model | Accuracy | Precision |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| Support Vector Machine | 97.78% | 97.52% |
| K-Nearest Neighbors | 90.52% | 100.00% |
| Multinomial Naive Bayes | 97.20% | 100.00% |
| Decision Tree | 92.75% | 82.47% |
| Logistic Regression | 95.65% | 96.97% |
| Random Forest | 97.29% | 97.41% |
| AdaBoost | 92.16% | 82.02% |
| Bagging Classifier | 95.65% | 86.61% |
| **Extra Trees Classifier** ⭐ | **97.78%** | **98.32%** |
| Gradient Boosting | 94.78% | 92.00% |
| XGBoost | 96.81% | 95.65% |

---

# 🏆 Best Model

After comparing all models,

## ⭐ Extra Trees Classifier

was selected because it achieved

- Accuracy → **97.78%**
- Precision → **98.32%**

It provided the best balance between overall accuracy and precision.

